===Alternative forms===
* In {{w|traditional Chinese}} (based on the modern character forms used in {{w|zh:國字標準字體|Taiwan}} and {{w|zh:常用字字形表|Hong Kong}}), the bottom left component is {{l|mul|朮}} ({{l|mul|𣎳}} with an additional dot at its top right corner).
* In mainland China (based on the {{w|Xin Zixing}} ({{lw|zh|新字形}}) standardized character forms), the bottom left component is {{l|mul|朩}} instead which is one stroke less.
* In Korean {{w|hanja}}, the bottom left component is {{l|mul|术}}, which is also the historical form found in the {{w|Kangxi dictionary}}.
* In Japanese {{w|shinjitai}} and Vietnamese [[Nôm]], the bottom left component is {{l|mul|木}} which is one stroke less.
* Three {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs}} exist for this character:
** <code>U+F970</code> corresponds to the Japanese {{w|kyūjitai}} form containing {{l|mul|术}} which is similar to the historical Kangxi form.
** <code>U+FA96</code> corresponds to the alternative Korean form which is similar to the Japanese {{w|shinjitai}} form containing {{l|mul|木}}.
** <code>U+2F8F5</code> is similar to the traditional form in Taiwan but has {{l|mul|𣎳}} (without dot at top right corner) instead of {{l|mul|朮}} as its bottom left component.

