==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the oracle bone script, it was an {{liushu|ic|nocap=y}} of a boar that had been impaled in the head.

In the seal script, the original compound was corrupted into {{zh-l|𣏂}} (sometimes written as {{zh-l|杀}}). It was also in the seal script that the {{Han compound|人|又|t1=person|t2=right hand|ls=p|nocap=y}}, which was later corrupted into {{zh-l|*殳|spear}} or {{zh-l|*攴}}, was added under the head of the boar to specify the killing was done by a person.

The modern-day character inherits this and can be thought of as a {{Han compound|𣏂|c1=p|殳|c2=s|t2=spear|ls=psc|nocap=yes}}.

